  "description": "Karl Harald Ossian Ericson was a Swedish city architect, born on January 3, 1890 in Ailanäs, Jämtland County, Sweden to lecturer Olof E. Ericson and Hanna Olsson. He graduated from KTH Royal Institute of Technology in 1915 and worked at various firms before starting his own business from 1922-1929. In 1929, he was appointed as the city architect of Borås, where he worked until his death. He was a member of Rotary and the Swedish Society for Town and Country Planning, and enjoyed sportfishing as a hobby."
